 "bio": "Russell Peters is a Canadian stand-up comedian, actor and producer of Indian descent whose material centres on cultural and racial observation drawn from his Indo-Canadian upbringing. He performed in Toronto from the late 1980s, and his 2004 set on the Canadian program Comedy Now became a viral hit on early YouTube, turning him into an international touring act in the 2000s. He became one of the worlds highest-paid comedians and the first comedian to headline a Netflix stand-up special.",
